column36: 6 mo Bil DXMM on 10/23, f/u with Hagen on 10/31, see Wong on 10/29.
column66: pt forgot PT appt, rescheduled to 7/19 at 9 am

column36: She called about seeing Dr. McDunn tomorrow and wondered if I could go. She needs AI refilled till May because she will be in China until end of April. She will also need to reschedule her appt with Dr. Monahan in March to May. And will need to ask about her head's scan result. I called clinic H and left a message for them to give to McDunn tomorrow.
column66: Husband called to ask for appt with Dr.McDunn. Scheduled it on 5/7 8am clinic H.
column96: She wanted to know if she is qualified for Mercy's Whole Women Whole Health benefit of free massages since she was diagnosed at Mercy.
column126: She received letter from No Wooden Nickel shown that she weren't eligible for assistance that was applied over a year ago.
column156: Couldn't find Chinese speaking PCP to schedule an appt, was getting transfer around back and forth until finally scheduled one at Near South Health Center.

column36: Ivy and Cindy accompanied pt to follow up with Dr. Perez. A lipoma was discovered and told pt to monitor for changes. If changes occur, to let Dr. Perez or navigators know. Dr. Perez will check for changes to the lipoma when it is time for follow up visit. Next follow up visit is scheduled for 9/21/16 at 7:30 DXMM and 8:30 with Dr. Perez.
column126: Pt had DXMM at 8:30-9:20. Saw Dr. Perez. Mammogram again in 6 months. 04/20/2017 next appointment.  Dr. Perez said everything was okay.
column156: Patient is here to fu with Dr. Wong. Dr.Wong examines her and everything looks fine. She need to continue taking the medication and need a bilateral DXMM in Oct. Scheduled DXMM in 10/23/2017 at 8am and fu with Dr. Wing in 11/1/2017 at 9:30
column186: f/u in a year with Shirazi on 7/18/18 at 10 am
column214: 1 year f/u, Lily will mail with time and appt.   10/24/18 9 am DXMM and 10:30 am Perez
column243: Answered questions and showed her Dr. Wong's new clinic location.

column36: patient came in for her 6 month f/u MMG from her lumpectomy.
column66: Patient came in for her 6 month fu with Dr. Perez. Everything looks fine from the MMG and examination from Dr. Perez. patient complains about the shape  of the nipple is different , wonder was it from radiation. Dr. Perez say it could be but she points out both nipples are about the same shape. Fu with Bilerteral MMG in 6 months ( 07/03/2017 at 9am) and fu with DR. perez in sept 27, 2017 10:15am.
column96: patient came in to see dr. wong for a fu apt . everything looks great, fu in 6 month in july 25 at 9am with a bilateral screening as well. dr. wong wrote an order for her scmm.
column126: she need to come see Dr. Wong 07/16/2019   DXMM 8/27/2018 7:30 am

column36: mouth problems are not caused by tamoxifen, advised pt should not stop taking it and should go see dentist.    Wong f/u on 1/12/16 at 10;15 am  Shirazi f/u on 4/6/16 between 9 to 11 am.
column66: Ann & Shuping accompany  See Dr. Wong in 7/5/2016 at 9am
column96: Ann & Shuping interpreted  f/u with Dr. Shirazi in 6 mths ( 10/11/2016 at 1pm)
column126: Shuping accompanied  3 mth f/u with Dr. Wong. She was out of medication for 10 days. Dr. Wong advised her to inform us (navigators) if she is out of pills so we can inform Dr. Wong.
column156: help her make appointment for bone scan and CBC test. 10/14/16 8:00am .come back see Wong Nov,1,2016
column186: patient came to see Dr. Shirazi for a 6 month follow up. Everything looks good. Patient complain about pain around her right side, doctor say it is due to some scarring tissues after the surgery. Follow up with Dr. Shirazi in 6 month ( April 11, 2017)
column214: Patient came to get her lab and a full body scan to find out about her back pain.
column243: Patient came in for her fu with Dr. Shirazi. Patient complains tightness on her chest area where the incision is and also her right arm can not lift too high up. Dr. Shirazi say it is normal. Patient say her gums are decreasing  from the gum line, Dr. Shirazi advise her to see a dentist, she needs a cleaning, her teeth might fall eventually if she doesn't take care of it. Fu in 1 year (4/11/18 at 9:30am ). Patty (the nurse) gave her one of the dentist's info in Bridgeport that accepts her insurances, if she's interesting.
column273: 1 year f/u with Shirazi on 4/16/19 at 10 am.  Shirazi advised pt to see ENT for tongue's ulcer/sore and possibly see dentist depend on ENT's advise. ENT Patel scheduled for 4/19 10  am, and follow up with Wong on 4/24 at 11 am.
column296: Saw ENT Dr. Patel - tongue lesion is not malignant, just need to f/u with dentist for extensive dental issues.

column36: She asked about pre-auth, coz it was wrong authorization and had to cancel again.  Change schedule for Robinson survivorship appt for her.
column66: Pre-auth explained and apologized, will submit a new one.
column96: new pre-auth is approved, will schedule thyroid update again.
column126: come  back see dr. Wong 04/16/18 and 2/01/18 that is her last time chemo. and than she can remove the port.
column186: Just helped her settled to wait for IR doc to check her port removal wound. She had to wait for almost 2 hrs to be seen.
column214: Scheduled next MMG and Hagen appt. Also scheduled Gyne for her, last Pap w/o HPV was 8/23/16
column243: Next Pap due Aug 2019, did not have HPV last time.   Need colon screening as well, pt says will do it when the weather is warmer.

column36: Today is the last day Radiation. see Dr. Wong 1/16/16
column66: she appointment see doctor Wong and Shirazi today.  Everything is ok, she need come back see Dr. Wong on 05/10 2016 10:00AM and see Dr. Shirazi 08/16/16 9:30am. six month F/U DXMM 04/20/16 9:30am
column126: Dr. Bower check the wound everything is okay.
column156: she need come back six months DXMM on Left side
column186: she need come back see Dr. Wong 8/09/16 and Oct/2016 need to come for SCMM on Right.
column214: she need come back see Dr. Shirazi on Feb, 14.2017 9:30am

column36: Surgery scheduled for 12/1, mastectomy with SLNB. Due to Her2+, she will continue with pertuzumab for a year after surgery.
column66: mastectomy with SLNB, took out 4 negative nodes.
column96: Dressing/wrapping was changed, explained and comforted her on drainage, dizziness, vomit, pain, etc. Provided post-op, drain, followup instruction.
column126: DR. Perez help her remove drain and she need to come back to F/U on Jan,7 /2016
column156: DR. Wong recommend she do the MUGA and Radiation. after MUGA back to see him on 01/05/16 9:45am.  she complain the wound red and pain so today has appointment to see residents too because Dr. Perez off. Resident check her wound and than give her prescription ant-inflammatory she need take a twice a day. come back to see Dr. Perez on 12/29/15 11:30am. and MUGA 7:45am
column186: she finish the MUGA and see DR. Perez she check the wound is fine and DR. Perez talk to DR. Wong she don't need to do the Radiation and chemo every three weeks.
column214: see Dr. Wong today she need to take Tamoxifen  every day and vitamin D. Come back see him 02/23/16 10:30am. Still need to Chemo until Aug.
column273: Dr. Perez write the prescription for her pain. come back May.
column296: Ann & Shuping interpreted  did a MUGA

column36: Shuping accompanied and interpreted  See Dr. Shirazi  for a weekly f/u on radiation. Skin color beginning to differentiate from the other side.
column66: Dr. Shirzai examined the right breast, everything looks good. Advised to put on lotion for a month. skin will be tanned in 3 weeks time and about 4-5 months, skin will start to lightened up. F/u in 1 month with Dr. Shirazi after radiation treatment.
column96: Dr. Wong write the prescription to order the pill for her, they will send it to her home than she need to call Alma Make an appointment to see Wong. she need to take twice a day every other two weeks. when she take the pill if her fingernail change color to red she need to call Alma or tell us.
column126: she need to come back see Dr. Shirazi six month F/U 3/9/2017 2:30 pm.
column156: Pt see dr. Wong on how to intake the the pills (Capecitabine 500mg and 100mg) after receiving them in the mail. Dr. Wong wants her to take 3 of the 500mg and 1 of the 100mg twice a day with meal for 7 days  on, 7 days off and then blood test. If pt experiencing redness on palm, fever, mouth sore, loose stools, or needle pain, pt needs to immediately stop taking the pill and contact the doctor. F/u with Dr. Wong on Oct 7, 2016 with lab.
column186: Patient came for her followup after taking the new medication. She had blood work done today as well before seeing Dr. Wong. She will continuing taking the medication (she will received the medicines on Tuesday due to the hurricane in Florida where it is shipped). She can have the port removed.
column214: called to remind patient for her lab work before she starts her medication. accompanied patient to get lab work done and see if her medication has arrived yet.
column243: she has removal port today,every thing ok . told her if the wound pain she can take Tylenol red or has fever need to go to emergency room. She will come back see Dr. Wong 11/11/16 8:00pm.
column273: 1 month f/u with Dr. Wong while taking the capectabine 500mg and 150mg. Dr. Wong examined her, everything is fine. she needs to continue to take the medication until Feb 2017(6months treatment). Afterwards there's no medication to take. Will continue to have bloodwork every 2 weeks before she starts to take the medication. F/u with Dr. Wong dec 5 with bloodwork.
column296: Patient is here for her 6 month DXMM fu.

column36: healing nicely. come back in 6 wks then schedule for tattoo in 1-2wks after that.
column126: tattoo in July, 3 mo after nipple reconstruction. Will try to get it paid through insurance, otherwise it is $250. pt can pay whatever they can afford or Dr. Scherile will pay for the rest.
column156: 6 mo Lt SCMM and f/u   4/5/17 at 9:30 am SCMM  4/18/18 at 9:30 am Hagen
column186: She is concern with a new lump that appeared a week ago at the same location of the old tumor.
column214: Scheduled appt with Hagen to decide the next step for the new lump.
column243: She is sent for same day U/S, then scheduled Bx for the next day.
column273: new lump is subQ but she insisted on the Bx to have a definite Dx.
column296: Result was given to pt and explain the next steps are MRI, CT, and Bone scans. Schedules were givent to her.

column36: Seen by Wong, advise to go to ER with dyspnea, chest pain, and swelling in extremities. Scheduled colonoscopy on 5/2 at 8:30, Wong on 10/1 at 8:15, and need gyne exam annually.
column96: Rt MM in June 29 2018, will call pt with result. Dec 2018 f/u with OV.
column126: ASCUS and HPY (-) 6/18/16, repeated cotesting today. Will call with result.
column156: Scheduled OPS for colonoscopy on 6/1 at noon, then f/u with Gupta on 6/27 at 9:30 am. Explained prep work and other f/u appt confirmations.
column214: Colonoscopy at OPS.   Need to reschedule with Wong on 10/1 at 8:15 am, will be in China 9/5 to 12/1. Need extra refill before going to China. Scheduled appt with PCP Najar on 6/27 8 am before Gupta's f/u appt at 9:30 am.
column243: She received phone call and not sure what it was for, so I called back for her. It was Gupta's office following up and remind her the f/u appt.
column273: She need to come for the SCMM next year. 6/30/2019

column36: 3/1/18 see Perez at 11:30am, next Lt SCMM in Sept 2018.
column66: changed 3/1 appt to 3/14 at 10:45 am with Perez.
column96: She should go to survivorships. Scheduled f/u with Hagen on 9/19 and Wong on 6/12.
column126: Rt mastectomy looking for soft prosthesis from ACS, normal size is 38A.
column214: her SCMM MMG is normal. she need to come back six month F/U see DR. Hagen and one year for the SCMM.
